  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Welder Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>The Welder Technician is responsible for performing welding and fabrication work on metal components and structures in accordance with engineering drawings, specifications, and safety standards. The role requires precision, technical skill, and adherence to quality and workplace safety requirements.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform welding work using appropriate techniques (e.g. MIG, TIG, ARC/Stick) on steel, stainless steel, aluminum, or other metals</li><li>Read and interpret engineering drawings, blueprints, and work instructions </li><li>Measure, cut, grind, and prepare materials prior to welding</li><li>Inspect welded joints to ensure quality, strength, and dimensional accuracy</li><li>Carry out minor fabrication, fitting, and assembly work as required</li><li>Operate welding equipment, hand tools, and power tools safely</li><li>Perform basic maintenance and housekeeping of welding equipment</li><li>Follow workplace safety procedures and use proper personal protective equipment (PPE)</li><li>Report defects, material issues, or safety concerns to supervisors</li><li>Support repair, modification, or installation works on-site or in the workshop</li><li>Comply with company quality standards and project timelines</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements & Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Proven experience as a Welder or Welder Technician</li><li>Relevant welding certification or technical qualification is preferred</li><li>Knowledge of different welding techniques and materials</li><li>Ability to read technical drawings and measurements accurately</li><li>Familiar with workplace safety and welding safety standards</li><li>Physically fit and able to work in industrial or site environments</li><li>Willingness to work overtime or on-site when required</li><li>Team player with good communication skills</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Skills (Advantage)</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in fabrication or structural welding</li><li>Ability to perform basic mechanical or fitting work</li><li>Experience working on construction, shipyard, manufacturing, or maintenance projects</li></ul><p><strong>Working Conditions</strong></p><ul><li>Workshop and/or site-based work</li><li>Exposure to heat, noise, and metalwork environments</li><li>PPE will be provided and required at all times</li><li>Expected to Start Work in March to April 2026</li></ul>",
